<subSubSection id="D6F548EEFE5073C863ECA0BD37ED1C42" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="46ACEC9FF77BBC04624CF33017B001D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C51208D06312BCA3210CDFEAAC6DE0EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
The taxon 
<taxonomicName id="716BE419A8F310F926A643371B384EFB" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Zhao &amp; Liu" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Fruhstorferia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fruhstorferia birmanica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birmanica">
<emphasis id="48BEDBC72EEC327B56688C7D1B2F0DA7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Fruhstorferia birmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described based on a pair of specimens from Ruby Mines, Burma (
<bibRefCitation id="10624698825534546F4096817A270A70" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930709487274" author="Arrow, GJ" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B1" refString="Arrow, GJ, 1907. Some new species and genera of lamellicorn Coleoptera from the Indian Empire (part 1). The Annals and Magazine of natural History, including Zoology, Botany and Geology Series 7 19(112): 347-359. https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930709487274" title="Some new species and genera of lamellicorn Coleoptera from the Indian Empire (part 1). The Annals and Magazine of natural History, including Zoology, Botany and Geology Series 7 19 (112): 347 - 359." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930709487274" year="1907">Arrow 1907</bibRefCitation>
). The lectotype has not yet been designated and the male illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="CFAE9E4011FF2FF6A203847065565DE9" author="Muramoto, R" journalOrPublisher="Kogane" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="12 - 16" refId="B21" refString="Muramoto, R, Araya, K, 2000. A new species of the genus Fruhstorferia Kolbe, 1894 from northern Thailand. Kogane 1: 12 - 16" title="A new species of the genus Fruhstorferia Kolbe, 1894 from northern Thailand." volume="1" year="2000">Muramoto and Araya (2000)</bibRefCitation>
has been erroneously fixed as holotype. According to Art. 74.7.1 (ICZN 1999), both specimens should be regarded as syntypes. The examination of both syntypes reveals that the female is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="2DC28A530DE67C74E38DB2FF137D0BB7" genus="D." lsidName="D. mizunumai" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="mizunumai">
<emphasis id="28245FEE621512F40E61656D866DC4AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. mizunumai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nagai &amp; Hirasawa, 1991. Therefore, a lectotype designation is necessary.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0DBC815738DA7213B159346FDC42CD18" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
The male genitalia of the lectotype (Figs 
<figureCitation id="193CC825F87AF90359082865EA8B662F" captionStart="Figures 7–10" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 10. Morphological details of Didrepanephorus Didrepanephorus species 7 head of holotype of D. tangzhaoyangi Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., oblique lateral view 8 head of D. birmanicus (Arrow, 1907) (Lectotype of Fruhstorferia birmanica Arrow, 1907), oblique lateral view, photo © Keita Matsumoto (NHMUK) 9 - 10 male genitalia of holotype of D. tangzhaoyangi 9 dorsal view 10 ventral view. Scale bar for genitalia only." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.75831.figures7-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668068" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B437933D732AA554E4EDF389741E42C1" captionStart="Figures 11–18" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 11 - 18. Type material of Didrepanephorus species. 11 - 15 male of D. birmanicus (Arrow, 1907) (Lectotype of Fruhstorferia birmanica Arrow, 1907) 16 - 18 female of D. mizunumai Nagai &amp; Hirasawa, 1991 (paralectotype of F. birmanica), habitus in dorsal view 11, 16 habitus in dorsal view 12, 17 habitus in lateral view 13 aedeagus showing parameres in dorsal view 14 aedeagus in dorsal view 15, 18 attached labels. All photos © Keita Matsumoto (NHMUK)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.75831.figures11-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668069" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">11-15</figureCitation>
) is partly damaged, which greatly complicates the comparison to its related 
<taxonomicName id="2EC5061C93E8D03BDF9745B756990570" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
. However, the similarity of this 
<taxonomicName id="73581B5B1A8B9E4B1C1366D637216235" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
to small-sized male of 
<taxonomicName id="ADEC40A22DF799BCD60A76379EAC57C5" genus="D." lsidName="D. yunnanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="yunnanus">
<emphasis id="A4E086E781C69D83B1A61FB89A881A64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. yunnanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ohaus, 1911) is still apparent in many external features, especially in the allied shape of terminal segment of maxillary palp, which is more expanded and compressed than other 
<taxonomicName id="1E42B26CD0C074FD13D5CD19409EDB8B" authorityName="Wood-mason" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="347761154F557B51AB33859078133092" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Didrepanephorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="7B1ABD3242E1D5829E9F0FE0DBBD1A80" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
. There is a strong concavity at the base of lower margin of mandible. The protrusion at lower margin is partly hidden under the labrum. These characters match the above definitions for 
<taxonomicName id="68025FE523450B97D2E19D1DD37EA126" authorityName="Wood-mason" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="14081C4BBB9988A9547B9B253D461C2E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Didrepanephorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, this 
<taxonomicName id="F3771E45EA3A6946DF3BBDD6451EDFBD" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="1E9D5577127C6BF523AB21C5678BE262" authorityName="Wood-mason" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1337FAFB09D2C53AD267DB6EF9463E2A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Didrepanephorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein. Among the five subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="F4F183CDA4504A5DDDEAA6BE4ED2A76A" genus="D." lsidName="D. yunnanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="yunnanus">
<emphasis id="BD23BD0275AA153C476ECC6E06E791A2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. yunnanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="5D10882D54FD40400EE77FA670338D91" genus="D." lsidName="D. y. subsp. yunnanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="y." subSpecies="yunnanus">
<emphasis id="9A0159583A03C0C774B7BD9F4B48EE13" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. y. yunnanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ohaus, 1911), 
<taxonomicName id="3DE4105B344CAAED38000362C6A6F134" genus="D." lsidName="D. y. subsp. clermonti" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="y." subSpecies="clermonti">
<emphasis id="0CC249E3DE4C7C611413F5C51FB0D6D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. y. clermonti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Benderitter, 1929, 
<taxonomicName id="61590BE1CC20878A9D619E318131FCF9" genus="D." lsidName="D. y. subsp. piaoacensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="y." subSpecies="piaoacensis">
<emphasis id="2CD5FF5CB25258DAEA2A2F91C7341826" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. y. piaoacensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nagai, 2004, 
<taxonomicName id="4862112A418A943252B19D43406729FB" genus="D." lsidName="D. y. subsp. wakaharai" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="y." subSpecies="wakaharai">
<emphasis id="053AFDB2035FD1A3C25BF9F8F9345005" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. y. wakaharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nagai, 2004, and 
<taxonomicName id="5FAC99F5A82137AEA67098B55535B9DF" genus="D." lsidName="D. y. subsp. kachinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="y." subSpecies="kachinensis">
<emphasis id="E52272938CCBEF70344A95DB53226B4D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. y. kachinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Muramoto, 2005, recognized by 
<bibRefCitation id="0F57C597BC35A08881471D1BA4B2ED0A" author="Muramoto, R" journalOrPublisher="Kogane" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="23 - 32" refId="B17" refString="Muramoto, R, 2005. Notes on Didrepanephorus yunnanus (Ohaus, 1911) and the genus Kibakoganea Nagai, 1984. Kogane 6: 23 - 32" title="Notes on Didrepanephorus yunnanus (Ohaus, 1911) and the genus Kibakoganea Nagai, 1984." volume="6" year="2005">Muramoto (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1E44C7D48799ED1714B7511096A534D" genus="D." lsidName="D. y. subsp. kachinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="y." subSpecies="kachinensis">
<emphasis id="CA48EF5CF95C2CAA84239505BCC88792" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. y. kachinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C27F41CD7533B176C72F88685C50E409" genus="D." lsidName="D. birmanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="birmanicus">
<emphasis id="1035D77C4B328A1625955D21B9DABB52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. birmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the generally reddish brown body in combination to the closest geographical distance. To fully understand the relation between the two 
<taxonomicName id="33E0843EA3C5C80803B2BE71C86AE40D" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
, examination of topotypical specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="2BD893879B037AD3562C114CEDA3A606" genus="D." lsidName="D. birmanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="birmanicus">
<emphasis id="8F7ED139D623863A1BD62AC5FFEBFCFA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. birmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with undamaged male genitalia is needed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F7FFD54864F1DA077CC6EE8FFC2167CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
This 
<taxonomicName id="F08F36DD82457BBBB6D474EDD6A02D2D" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
was partly misinterpreted and the name was previously applied to two different 
<taxonomicName id="27133F0B737A1458A03CF2AC47D65DE3" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
(see below). This 
<taxonomicName id="C954B0F24F003C2120D067E0D0544B0E" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
is so far only known from the lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ED800C453B178467C679183E42EAD986" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E0B48C8889066D316814FC4EDA894470" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C2E5AF8217CFFCD62010D17B882FE667" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Myanmar (Mandalay Region: Mogok).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
